  <title>Cogl.vector3_equal_with_epsilon</title>
  <synopsis><code mime="text/x-gjs">
function vector3_equal_with_epsilon(vector0: Number(gfloat), vector1: Number(gfloat), epsilon: Number(gfloat)): <link xref="Cogl.Bool">Cogl.Bool</link> {
    // Gjs wrapper for cogl_vector3_equal_with_epsilon()
}
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>Compares the components of two vectors using the given epsilon and
returns TRUE if they are the same, using an internal epsilon for
comparing the floats.</p>  <p>Each component is compared against the epsilon value in this way:
|[
  if (fabsf (vector0-&gt;x - vector1-&gt;x) &lt; epsilon)
]|</p>
  <p>Since 1.4</p>
<terms>
<item>
<title><code>vector0</code></title>
  <p>The first 3 component vector you want to compare</p>
</item>
<item>
<title><code>vector1</code></title>
  <p>The second 3 component vector you want to compare</p>
</item>
<item>
<title><code>epsilon</code></title>
  <p>The allowable difference between components to still be
          considered equal</p>
</item>
<item>
<title><code>Returns</code></title>
  <p>TRUE if the vectors are equal else FALSE.</p>
</item>
